slush lamp
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[used elsewhere but recorded earliest in NZ] a basic light source, being a tin filled with fat in which a wick is placed.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
