Date: 0/0/1898
Source: Austral English
Author: MORRIS
Vol / Page: 421
Edition:
Quote: a lamp made by filling an old tin with fat and putting a rag in for wick. The word, though not exclusively Australian, is more common in the Australian bush than elsewhere. Compare English <i>slush-horn</i>, horn for holding grease;<i> slush-pot,</i> pot for holding grease, etc.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1961
Source: Friends in Chains
Author: HENDERSON
Vol / Page: 189
Edition:
